<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Minimal entitlements for the CodeBurn menubar app.

        Sandbox is intentionally OFF: the app must spawn the user's `codeburn`
        CLI (Homebrew/npm/etc.), read Claude/Codex credentials from the user's
        Keychain, and persist refresh-token caches under
        ~/Library/Application Support/CodeBurn/. None of this fits inside a
        sandbox without temporary-exception entitlements that defeat the
        sandbox's purpose for our threat model.

        Hardened Runtime is ON (selected via `codesign --options=runtime`).
        That alone gives us:
            - DYLD_INSERT_LIBRARIES blocked
            - Library validation enforced
            - JIT, allow-unsigned-executable-memory, allow-dyld-environment
              all default-OFF (we don't enable them below)
            - Apple Events / Audio / Camera / Mic / Photos / Calendars /
              Contacts / Reminders / Documents / Downloads / Location are all
              implicitly denied unless we add the corresponding entitlement.

        We grant exactly two:
            - cs.allow-jit / cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory: NOT set,
              so a tampered Foundation/AppKit dylib cannot inject code.
            - cs.disable-library-validation: NOT set, so loaded frameworks
              must be Apple-signed or share our team identifier (when we
              eventually have a Developer ID).

        When a paid Apple Developer ID becomes available, replace the ad-hoc
        codesign step in mac/Scripts/package-app.sh with a Developer ID Application
        signature and run `xcrun notarytool submit` to notarize. The
        entitlements below do NOT need to change for that move; they are
        already compatible with notarization.
    -->

    <!-- Required by SMAppService for login-item registration. Not strictly an entitlement,
         but documenting here that we explicitly do NOT request the auto-launch one because
         SMAppService.mainApp uses the bundle's SMLoginItem property already. -->

    <!-- Network usage: the menubar talks to api.github.com (UpdateChecker) and
         platform.claude.com (Claude OAuth refresh). No exception entitlement
         needed for an unsandboxed app — outbound TCP works without one. -->
</dict>
</plist>
